President Muhammadu Buhari, Thursday evening, condemned the armed attack on Mangu council area of Plateau State and ordered security agencies to unravel what went wrong. Suspected cattle rustlers had on Wednesday reportedly killed 12 persons in Kombun community in Mangu council area. However, condemning the killing in a statement issued by his Senior Special Assistant on Median and Publicity, Mallam Garba Shehu, President Buhari said he had been in touch with the Plateau State governor, Mr. Simon Lalong and the military in respect of the development. “President Muhammadu Buhari strongly condemns the gunmen attack on Mangu Local Government in Plateau State and is in contact with the Governor, Simon Lalong and the military, police and other security agencies in the state to ascertain details of what happened and what can be done to forestall a future occurrence. “President Buhari said he is shocked and grieved by the incident and has urged security agencies in the state to increase vigilance to stop further attacks on innocent communities”, the statement said.